## 0과 1만 필터링


```python copy
import numpy as np
def filter_dataset(x, y, neg_cls, pos_cls):
    m = (y == pos_cls) | (y == neg_cls)
    x = x[m]
    y = y[m]
    y = np.where(y == neg_cls, 0, 1) # neg_cls는 0, 아니면 1
    return x, y
```



```python copy
x_train2, y_train2 = filter_dataset(x_train, y_train, 0, 1)
```

## 모델


```python copy
from tensorflow.keras.layers import *
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    Flatten(), # 28x28 이미지를 평평하게 만들어 784 차원 벡터로 
    Dense(1, activation='sigmoid') # 최종적으로 1개의 출력(0~1 범위)
])
```


학습 설정


```python copy
model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
```


훈련


```python copy
result = model.fit(x_train2, y_train2, validation_split=0.1, epochs=10)
```

## 훈련 방법 변경

### Early Stopping


```python copy
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    Flatten(),
    Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
])
model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

result = model.fit(x_train2, y_train2, validation_split=0.1, epochs=100,
                  callbacks=[tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(patience=5)])
```


## 자동 저장


```python copy
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    Flatten(),
    Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
])
model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

model.fit(x_train2, y_train2, epochs=100, validation_split=0.1,
    callbacks=[tf.keras.callbacks.ModelCheckpoint(
                'checkpoints.weights.h5', # 파일명
                monitor="val_accuracy", # 정확도 기준
                save_best_only=True, # 이전보다 좋은 결과만 저장
                save_weights_only=True, # 파라미터만 저장
)])

```


불러오기


```python copy
model.load_weights('checkpoints.weights.h5')
```


## Adam으로 학습


```python copy
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    Flatten(),
    Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
])
model.compile(
    optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
    loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
model.fit(x_train2, y_train2, epochs=3, validation_split=0.1)
```
